20don't%20hallucinate%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-cofounder-says-ai-errors-are-necessary-tradeoff-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoccasional%20chatbot%20errors%20are%20a%20necessary%20%26quot%3Btradeoff%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThese%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20train%20them%20to%20never%20hallucinate%20%E2%80%94%20they%20will%20become%20very%2C%20very%20worried%20about%20making%20mistakes%20and%20they%20will%20say%2C%20'I%20don't%20know%20the%20context'%20to%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20It's%20up%20to%20developers%20to%20determine%20when%20occasional%20errors%20are%20acceptable%20in%20an%20AI%20product.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20hallucinations%20have%20gotten%20some%20tech%20giants%20into%20sticky%20situations%2C%20such%20as%20last%20year%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-fake-legal-case-ai-georgia-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20was%20sued%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20radio%20host%20for%20generating%20a%20false%20legal%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamaswamy%20said%20that%2C%20especially%20for%20%26quot%3Bcritical%20applications%26quot%3B%20like%20analyzing%20a%20company's%20financial%20data%2C%20AI%20tools%20%26quot%3Bcan't%20make%20mistakes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20insidious%20thing%20about%20hallucinations%20is%20not%20that%20the%20model%20is%20getting%205%25%20of%20the%20answers%20wrong%2C%20it's%20that%20you%20don't%20know%20which%205%25%20is%20wrong%2C%20and%20that's%20like%20a%20trust%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Snowflake%20CEO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaris%20Gultekin%2C%20Snowflake's%20head%20of%20AI%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20AI%20hallucinations%20are%20the%20%26quot%3Bbiggest%20blocker%26quot%3B%20for%20generative%20AI%20to%20front-end%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20generative%20AI%20is%20being%20deployed%20for%20internal%20use%20cases%20only%2C%20because%20it's%20still%20challenging%20for%20organizations%20to%20control%20exactly%20what%20the%20model%20is%20going%20to%20say%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20results%20are%20accurate%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Gultekin%20said%20AI%20accuracy%20will%20improve%2C%20with%20companies%20now%20able%20to%20put%20guardrails%20on%20the%20models'%20output%20to%20restrict%20what%20AI%20can%20say%2C%20what%20tones%20are%20allowed%2C%20and%20other%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BModels%20increasingly%20understand%20these%20guardrails%2C%20and%20they%20can%20be%20tuned%20to%20protect%20against%20things%20like%20bias%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20access%20to%20diverse%20data%20and%20sources%2C%20Gultekin%20said%20that%20AI%20will%20increasingly%20become%20more%20accurate%20and%20much%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bbacklash%26quot%3B%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Bmitigated%20one%20successful%20use%20case%20at%20a%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESnowflake's%20CEO%20said%20that%20while%20he%20would%20want%20100%25%20accuracy%20for%20certain%20AIs%20like%20financial%20chatbots%2C%20there%20are%20other%20cases%20where%20users%20would%20%26quot%3Bhappily%20accept%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20mistakes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Ramaswamy%20said%20that%20people%20send%20him%20a%20lot%20of%20articles%20to%20read.%20When%20he%20inputs%20them%20into%20a%20chatbot%20like%20Claude%20or%20ChatGPT%2C%20he%20doesn't%20mind%20if%20the%20summary%20isn't%20always%20exactly%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20huge%20deal%20because%20it's%20just%20the%20time%20saving%20that%20I%20get%20from%20not%20actually%20having%20to%20crank%20through%20the%20article%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20so%20much%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.co